===Noun===
{{en-noun|?}}
# {{lb|en|rare}} A {{l|en|spasm}} experienced whilst attempting to use a shaving {{l|en|razor}}.
#* '''1904''', [[w:Hermann Oppenheim|Hermann Oppenheim]], ''Diseases of the Nervous System'' ([[w:J. B. Lippincott & Co.|J.B. Lippincott Co.]]), <span class="plainlinks">[http://books.google.co.uk/books?id=Emp_pbrbXlYC&q=xyrospasm&dq=xyrospasm&hl=en&ei=MoUCTuyRAoOv8gOTiNjEAg&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=2&ved=0CDAQ6AEwAQ page 859]</span>
#*: I have seen in two cases a barbers’ cramp (keirospasm or '''xyrospasm''') — ''i.e.'', a spastic contraction of the muscles of the hand and fingers, which came on in a barber at every attempt to use a razor.
